it was either the 4th of July morning or the day before the 4th of
July, correct? That's what this transcript indicates, true?

A. That's what is says there, yes.

Q. And you, of course, say now, that you would never say -- have said
that it was the 3rd or the 4th of July, correct?

A. Correct.

Q. Okay.

And you don't know why that it appears in two places in the matter of
