<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles: O.J. Simpson Transcripts (November)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000">
<A HREF="/map/top-casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/top-casefiles.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<H2>The O.J. Simpson Civil Trial Transcripts: November</H2>

<P>NOTE: Some of these files are quite long (200k+) and may take a few minutes to load. If you prefer, you may download a compressed (zipped) version of the file to your hard drive. (You'll need an <A HREF="/download/utility/">unzipping utility</A> to decompress the file).</P>

<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>

<P><A HREF="nov01.html"><B>Friday, November 1</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov01.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
Further testimony from retired LAPD Detective Tom Lange, as well as from his partner, Det. Vannatter.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Thomas Lange, Philip Vannatter</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov04.html"><B>Monday, November 4</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov04.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
Testimony covered the collection of evidence from the crime scene.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Gregory Matheson, Dennis Fung</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov05.html"><B>Tuesday, November 5</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov05.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
Testimony about blood tests conducted on items taken from O.J. Simpson's home, as well as testimony about hair and fiber evidence collected at the crime scene.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Dennis Fung, Susan Brockbank</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov06.html"><B>Wednesday, November 6</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov06.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
Testimony about O.J. Simpson's gloves and shoes.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Michael Romano, Bill Renken (Transcript Read), Richard Rubin</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov07.html"><B>Thursday, November 7</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov07.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
Witnesses testify about cuts to O.J. Simpson's hands and evidence from the hotel room in Chicago.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Dr. Robert Huizenga, Donald Dutton, Park Dietz</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov08.html"><B>Friday, November 8</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov08.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
Plaintiff's pathology expert on the stand.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Dr. Werner Spitz</I></P>

<P><B>Monday, November 11</B><BR>
No Transcript; Court not in session.</P>

<P><A HREF="nov12.html"><B>Tuesday, November 12</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov12.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
More from pathologist and direct testimony from FBI hair & fiber expert.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Dr. Werner Spitz, Douglas Deedrick</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov13.html"><B>Wednesday, November 13</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov13.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
More hair & fiber evidence and the start of DNA-related testimony.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Douglas Deedrick, Robin Cotton</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov14.html"><B>Thursday, November 14</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov14.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
More DNA evidence including testimony from California Department of Justice criminalists.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Robin Cotton, Renee Montgomery, Gary Sims</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov15.html"><B>Friday, November 15</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov15.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
The defense questions California Department of Justice criminalist Gary Sims about whether blood evidence could have been planted.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Gary Sims</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov18.html"><B>Monday, November 18</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov18.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
Further testimony about possible evidence contamination, as well as preliminary testimony about domestic violence.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Collin Yamauchi, John Edwards, Sharyn Gilbert, Mark Day, Robert Lerner</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov19.html"><B>Tuesday, November 19</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov19.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
The world's most famous house guest takes the stand.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Robert Lerner, Michael Stevens, Brian Kaelin</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov20.html"><B>Wednesday, November 20</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov20.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
Testimony from the limousine driver who took Simpson to the airport on the night of the murders.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Allan Park, William Bodziak</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov21.html"><B>Thursday, November 21</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov21.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
Continued testimony from FBI footwear expert.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> William Bodziak</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov22.html"><B>Friday, November 22</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov22.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
The defendant begins his testimony.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Orenthal James Simpson</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov25.html"><B>Monday, November 25</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov25.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
More testimony from the defendant.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Orenthal James Simpson</I></P>

<P><A HREF="nov26.html"><B>Tuesday, November 26</B></A><BR>
<I><A HREF="nov26.zip">Download a zipped version</A></I><BR>
The final day of direct examination of the defendant by the plaintiffs' lawyers. Court recessed early for the Thanksgiving break.<BR>
<I><B>Witnesses:</B> Orenthal James Simpson</I></P>

<P><B>Wednesday, November 27</B><BR>
No Transcript; Court not in session.</P>

<P><B>Thursday, November 28</B><BR>
No Transcript; Court not in session.</P>

<P><B>Friday, November 29</B><BR>
No Transcript; Court not in session.</P>

