<H2>Small Business Related Links</H2>

<P><A HREF="http://rampages.onramp.net/~fwbac">Fort Worth Business Assistance Center</A><BR>
This site offers a variety of resources for small businesses, including free assistance for entrepreneurs with questions.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.eotw.com">Entrepreneurs on the Web</A><BR>
Much of this site is under construction, but it's still worth a visit. You'll find business services and opportunities, financial information, magazines and more.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.ustreas.gov/treasury/services/services.html">The Department of Treasury, Small Business Opportunities</A><BR>
This site focuses on small, minority-owned and women-owned businesses. It links to Treasury Information files and lists of specialists in different fields. One section contains information on topics such as auctions for seized property and foreign asset controls.  </P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.sbaonline.sba.gov/">The Small Business Administration (SBA)</A><BR>
This government site is geared to the needs of small businesses. It links to government, commercial, financial, educational and general interest sites. It also provides extensive information about the SBA.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://ioma.com/ioma/">The Institute of Management and Administration (IOMA)</A><BR>
IOMA contains an extensive list of business resources and sample articles from its newsletters. Topics include credit management, insurance and risk, legal resources and more.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://ny_sbdc.ca.sunycentral.edu//sbdcnet.htm">Small Business Development Centers</A><BR>
This site links to regional small business development sites.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www-far.npr.gov/VDOB/">US Business Advisor</A><BR>
The US Business Advisor lists government services and information for businesses. It links to important laws and regulations, such as taxes, immigration, labor, environmental rules, and more. You can also send messages to President Clinton and Vice-President Gore.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.service.com/tcc/">The Company Corporation</A><BR>
This site might also be called "Incorporate 101."  As the (self-proclaimed) "largest online incorporation service in the world," The Company Corporation answers questions about the costs, structures and taxes involved in incorporating. They will even help you set up your own corporation online.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://nmq.com/">Net Marquee</A><BR>
NetMarquee is a resource for emerging businesses, family-owned firms and start-up companies. It offers news, trends, guidance, and research from outside experts, journalists and business people.</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.webcom.com/~seaquest/">The Small Business Resource Center</A><BR>
A guide on how to start and run a small business, including a collection of reports, links to related sites, and an illustrated catalog of books and tapes. This site also offers a free marketing channel for self-published authors with materials for business owners.</P>

