<H2>The Legal Helpline</H2>

<P><FONT SIZE="+2">W</FONT>elcome to the Legal Helpline, a free public forum where qualified lawyers answer your questions about the law. We've revamped the Helpline to make it easier to use for both you and our panelists. You can browse questions that have already been answered by clicking on one of the categories below. To submit a question, use our online <A HREF="form.html">submission form</A>.</P>

<P>Please remember that our panelists are volunteers. Though we would like to answer every question quickly, that isn't always possible.</P>

<P>We might also recommend several other areas on this site and others where you can look for help in answering your question. You can go to our collection of material on <A HREF="/legalhelp/business/">Small Business</A> legal issues, <A HREF="/legalhelp/family/">Family Law</A>, and <A HREF="/legalhelp/elder/">Elder Law</A>. You can also go to the collection of <A HREF="http://www1.counsel.com/lawlinks/lawlinks.html">legal research sites</A> compiled by <A HREF="http://www.counsel.com/">Counsel Connect</A>, our sister company. For downloadable legal forms, go to <A HREF="http://www.quickforms.com/">QuickForms</A>. Also, the <A HREF="http://www.nolo.com/">Nolo Press</A> site contains useful information on a variety of consumer and small business law topics. Much of that material is free, and there are also books and other material that can be purchased there.</P>

<P>Also, please take a moment to read our <A HREF="/legalhelp/helpline/about.html">introduction to the Legal Helpline</A> and <A HREF="/legalhelp/helpline/guidelines.html">guidelines for asking questions</A> and to meet our <A HREF="panelists.html">panelists</A>.</P>

<P><FONT SIZE="-1"><B>Please read our disclaimer:</B><BR> <TT>The Legal Helpline is designed to provide interesting information, and make you a more informed consumer of legal services. The answers given here by our editors and panelists are intended as general discussions of law and education only and are not intended as legal advice. Because the Legal Helpline is an open discussion forum, your postings will not be confidential and you should not post the specific facts of your case, nor will the resulting discussions constitute the formation of a lawyer-client relationship.</P>

<P>Legal problems can be very serious and you should not rely on online legal discussions in making decisions about your own particular legal situation. Please consult your own attorney before making any decisions about your own legal matters. Accepting the terms of this disclaimer is a condition for visiting and/or using the Legal Helpline.</P></FONT></TT>

