<H2>Legal Services For Older People</H2> 

<P>All states are required to make funding available for free legal services on non-criminal matters for people over age 60. Not all cases can be handled, but your local Area Agency on Aging can direct you to the people in your area who provide these services.</P>

<P>You might also get assistance from local law school legal aid clinics and local bar association programs that provide legal services for the elderly.</P>

<P>Other sources of assistance and information include:</P>

<P><B>American Association of Retired Persons</B><BR>
601 E Street, NW<BR>
Washington, DC  20049<BR>
800-424-3410</P>

<P><B>American Bar Association Commission on Legal Problems of the Elderly</B><BR>
1800 M Street, NW<BR>
Suite 200<BR>
Washington, DC  20036</P>

<P><B>American Society on Aging</B><BR>
