<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles: Menendez</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/top-casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/top-casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>California v. Lyle and Erik Menendez</H2>

<P><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/casefiles/menendez.gif" ALT="Photo" ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE="5" BORDER="0">The State Bar of California and the Los Angeles district attorney are investigating defense lawyer Leslie Abramson for alleged misconduct in the retrial of Lyle and Erik Menendez.</P>

<P>State Bar spokeswoman Anne Charles announced the probes Nov. 16. She said they were prompted by the testimony of defense psychologist Dr. William Vicary, who said that Abramson, Erik Menendez's attorney, ordered him to alter his notes and threatened him to take him off the case if he disobeyed.</P>

<P>Abramson has said Dr. Vicary's account was untrue but acknowledged asking him to clarify ambiguous statements and to cover notes that infringed on doctor-patient privilege or concerned subjects barred by the judge.</P>

<P>The Menendez brothers were convicted of first-degree murder on March 20, 1996, for the shotgun killings of their parents, Jose and Kitty Menendez. They are serving life prison terms without the possibility of parole.Lyle is held at the California Correctional Institution at Tehachapi. Erik is at the California State Prison in Sacramento County.</P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<P><A HREF="summaries/"><B>The Trial - Week by Week</B></A></P>

<P><A HREF="transcripts/"><B>Trial Transcripts</B></A></P>

<P><A HREF="documents/"><B>Documents from the Trial</B></A></P>

<P><B><A HREF="/discuss/gateway.html">Talk Back!</A></B><BR>
What do you think of the sentence in the Menendez case? Do you think they have a chance on appeal? Join other Menendez watchers in our <a href="/discuss/gateway.html">discussion group</A>. (If you haven't signed up for our discussion groups, you can <a href=/register/>register now</a>.)</P>

