<BR CLEAR=ALL>



<H2>Answer to Last Week's Question</H2>


<P><B><FONT SIZE="+1">Question:</FONT></B><BR>

In 1656 in Boston, Massachusetts colony, two Quaker women were charged with being witches. The Boston council ordered all their books to be burned in the public market by the city's hangman. After five weeks of imprisonment, it was decided they were not witches, and they were released. What were their names?<P>


<P><B><FONT SIZE="+1">Answer:</FONT></B><BR>
Ann Austin and Mary Fisher.<P> 


<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>

