<html><title>Court TV Presents - Mandatory Allegiance</title><body bgcolor=ffffff vlink=ff0000><center><img width=517 height=142 src=/graphics/ctv/chall.gif></center>␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀<blockquote><H2>Mandatory Allegiance</H2><b>It's early in the 1940s. West Virginia requires that students in its schools salute the flag and recite the Pledge of Allegiance every morning in order to attend public school.  Walter Barnette, a Jehovah's Witness, goes to court to challenge this law on behalf of his children and others in similar situations. He argues that the state's requirement violates the Bill of Rights of the Constitution. Who should win?</B><P> <a name="tab"><H2>First. . .</H2></a><font size=+1> <br clear=left><B><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/button.gif alt=" * "><a href="casef2.htm">Review Background and Context</a><br clear=left><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/button.gif alt=" * "><a href="casef3.htm">Get More Facts</a><br clear=left><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/button.gif alt=" * "><a href="casef4.htm">Review Other Cases and Authorities</a><br clear=left><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/button.gif alt=" * "><a href="casef5.htm">Consider Possible Arguments</a><br clear=left><H2>Then. . .</H2><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/button.gif alt=" * "><B><a href="argue.htm">Present an  Argument for One Side or the Other</a><br clear=left></font><H2>Or. . .</H2><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/redbutt.gif alt=" * "><B><a href="casef6.htm">Decide the case for Mr. Barnette</a><br><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/redbutt.gif alt=" * "><a href="casef7.htm">Decide the case for the State</a></font></B><br clear=left></font><H4><a href=/cases/direct.htm><I>Brief Instructions</I></a></H4><a  href=/cases/><I>Courtroom Challen