<html><TITLE> Court TV Presents - Interrogation Rights</TITLE><body bgcolor=ffffff vlink=ff0000><center><img width=517 height=142 src=/graphics/ctv/chall.gif></center>␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀<blockquote><H2>Police Interrogation - A Right to Know Your Rights?</H2> <B>It's 1963. The police bring a defendant, Ernest Arthur, to the police station for questioning in connection with a kidnapping and rape. He is put in a line-up, where the victim identifies him. During subsequent interrogation, the defendant confesses and is formally arrested.  He is then tried and convicted.<P>The defendant argues that his confession should not have been admitted at trial because the police failed to advise him of his right to a lawyer before they interrogated him. The State maintains there is no such automatic right.  Who is right?</B><P> <a name=tab><H2>First. . .</H2></a><font size=+1> <br clear=left><B><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/button.gif alt=" * "> <a href=reviewb.htm>Review Background  Information</a><br clear=left> <img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/button.gif alt=" * "> <a href=facts.htm>Get More Facts</a><br clear=left><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/button.gif alt=" * "> <a href=other.htm>Review Other Cases and Authorities</a><br clear=left><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/button.gif alt=" * "> <a href=parg.htm>Consider Possible Arguments</a><br clear=left><H2>Then. . .</H2><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/button.gif alt=" * "><B> <a href=arg.htm>Present an Argument for One Side or the Other</a></B><br clear=left></font><H2>Or. . .</H2><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/redbutt.gif alt=" * "><B><a href=case7.htm>Decide the case for Ernest Arthur</a></B><br clear=left><img width=33 height=31 align=middle src=/graphics/ctv/redbutt.gif alt=" * "><B><a href=case6.