<A HREF="/ctv-bin/goto.cgi?http://www.nabisco.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 ALT="Nabisco" SRC="/graphics/ctv/advert/nabisco.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT VSPACE=20 HSPACE=9></A>

<H2>Court TV Educational Programming</H2>



<BR>

<H3><A NAME="class">Class Action</A></H3>



<p><b>September</b></p>



<p><b>"The 1996 National High School Mock Trial Championship"</b></p>



Highlights of the final competition between the two best high school teams in the country. The teams consist of high school students who act as both the attorneys and the witnesses when arguing a fictional case. Throughout the show other students talk about their trial strategy and their opinions on the case.</p>



<P><A HREF="septsg.html">September Study Guide</A></P>



<p><b>October</b></p>



<p><b>"AIDS: Its Side Effects on America"</b></p>

Most of us know how seriously AIDS can affect our health, but how has AIDS affected our laws and the way we live? Court TV uses real trials and interviews to examine issues such as discrimination, the distribution of drugs, and even how AIDS has been used as a weapon to show how AIDS issues have effected changes to our laws. Outside of the courts, Court TV interviews professionals about changes they have had to make on the job because of the AIDS virus. </p>



<P><A HREF="octsg.html">October Study Guide</A></P>







<b><p>November</b></p>

<p><b>"Getting Physical"</b><p>

A look at the increasing evidence of emotional and physical abuse in teenage dating relationships.  Most people are now aware of the issue of domestic violence in our society, but there is increasing evidence of abuse among teenagers as well.  This program features an in-depth look at some of the early signs of relationship abuse, and how it can escalate into physical violence.  Court TV interviews students and teachers, and highlights a counselor who educates teenagers about what is and what is not acceptable behavior between boyfriends and girlfriends.</p>



<P><A HREF=novsg.html>November Study Guide</a><p>





<p><b>December</b></p>

<b><p>"A White Supremacist on Trial: Murder or Self-Defense?"</b></p>

Self-avowed white supremacist George David Loeb admits he shot and killed a black navy veteran, who had just returned from the Persian Gulf War, in a parking lot in Florida during an argument. The prosecution claims it was a result of Loeb's hatred of blacks. </p>



<P><A HREF=decsg.html>December Study Guide</a><p>



<P>Class Action airs every Saturday morning at 4am ET.</P>



<P><B>About Class Action</B><br>

Class Action is a series of specials, intended for viewing by students in grades 6 though 12, that deal with legal and social issues that affect our society. Its objective is to familiarize students with important issues our courts are faced with on a daily basis. The programs encourage discussion on important legal and social issues and the role of our judicial system in settling disputes.</P>



<P>To receive a free Class Action Study Guide, call: 1-800-333-7649</P>



<P>For more information, write to:<br>

Court TV<br>

Class Action<br>

600 Third Avenue<br>

New York, NY  10016</P>



<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT><BR>

