<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<h2>Videos: The O.J. Simpson Trial</h2>

<P><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/store/oj-video.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=20>
<B>An exclusive home video collection featuring the most newsworthy coverage of the case of California v. Simpson featuring trial footage and reporting by Court TV during its live in-depth coverage of the trial. Each video will include explanations of the law, rules of evidence and procedural technicalities, along with expert commentary and analysis of both prosecution and defense strategies. <I>(VHS, approx. 60 minutes each)</I></P>

<P>Volume 1: Background and Opening Statements. Both teams present their sides of the case.</P>

<P>Volume 2: The Prosecution Case: Step by step, the prosecution team, led by Marcia Clark, presents evidence which allegedly points to Mr. Simpson's guilt, including a bloody glove found at the defendant's home and analysis of blood stains found at the murder scene and on the defendant's Ford Bronco.</P>

<P>Volume 3: The Defense Case: The defense team, led by Johnnie Cochran, presents a different point of view and raises controversial questions: Did detectives botch the case with their sloppy investigation? Did racist police officers intentionally plant evidence?</P>

<P>Volume 4: Closing Statements and the Verdict: How did the jury decide the outcome of the case?</P>

<P>Price: $12.95 each.</P>

