<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG
SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A> <BR
CLEAR=ALL> <P>This statement was issued by O.J. Simpson after a family
court judge's <A HREF="custodyrule.html">Dec. 21, 1996 ruling</A>,
awarding him custody of the two children he had with Nicole Brown
Simpson. <I>Please note: the custody battle is a separate action from
the wrongful death suit.</I></P> <HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT> <PRE> 
"On behalf of myself and the entire Simpson family, we would like to make
this first and final statement to the press regarding my daughter
Sydney and my son Justin.

"We are all so very grateful to have the children home again where they
want to be.

"We would like to thank Lou and Juditha Brown for doing the best they
could during a very difficult time and fully expect them to continue
as active grandparents.

"All the independent mental health professionals who were appointed by
the court in this case have all agreed and counseled both families
that any further exploitation of the kids, or any further commentary
regarding the children, would be detrimental and not in the children's
best interests.

"Therefore, we would ask the media and the public to allow my children
their privacy and to live in as normal an environment as possible.

-O.J. Simpson

