<HTML>    
<HEAD>    
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>    
</HEAD>    
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000"    
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">    
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG    
SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV    
Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>    
<P>   
 
Since "no reasonable jury could find that Simpson has met burden of proof" to establish  
that blood evidence was planted, the only purpose presenting such evidence could serve is  
to "unnecessarily prolong the trial, confuse the issues, and mislead,"  the jury with  
argument that the...Bronco blood...was planted," Daniel Petrocelli, attorney for Fredric  
Goldman, states in this Aug. 26, 1996 pretrial motion.</P>  
 
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>    
<PRE>   
MITCHELL, SILBERBERG & KNUPP,  LLP  
DANIEL M. PETROCELLI (State Bar No. 97802)  
EDWARD M. MEDVENE (State Bar No. 32227)  
THOMAS P LAMBERT (State Bar No. 50952)  
