<HEAD> 
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE> 
</HEAD> 
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" 
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG 
SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV 
Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A> 
<P>
Stating that "the death of Nicole Brown Simpson bears none of the traditional signs of 
spousal homicide," the defense asks the judge to bar the plaintiffs from introducing 
evidence of domestic discord in the Simpson marriage. This would include the Oct. 25, 
1993 call to 911 and the "Zlomsowitch incident," when O.J. Simpson allegedly spied on 
his wife engaging in sex with another man. The defense contends that "evidence that a 
defendant has previously committed crimes or other bad acts is not admissible to prove 
how the defendant acted on a particular occasion, or to prove his propensity to commit 
the offense with which he had been charged," under the California Evidence Code. The 
defense claims that the plaintiffs' objective with this evidence is to unfairly prejudice the 
jury against Simpson. This pretrial motion was filed Aug. 26, 1996. </P> 

<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT> 
<PRE>
 
ROBERT C. BAKER, ESQ., BAR ID #49255 
MELISSA S. BLUESTEIN, ESQ., BAR ID #130055 
PHILLIP A. BAKER, ESQ., BAR ID #169571 
