<HTML> 
<HEAD> 
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE> 
</HEAD> 
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" 
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG 
SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV 
Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A> 
<P>
The defense argues that the introduction of evidence of O.J. Simpson's alleged drug use 
or adultery would be inadmissible in the civil action because it's immaterial and would be 
prejudicial. Simpson's lawyers accuse the plaintiffs of attempting "character 
assassination" on their client. Though Al Cowlings admits that he saw Simpson use 
cocaine, the defense points out that that was more than seven years before the murders 
and that Simpson has no criminal record for drug use. In regard to allegations of 
infidelity, the defense claims that these are irrelevant because the Simpsons were 
divorced and had not been living together for more than two years before the murders. 
This is the Aug. 26, 1996 pretrial motion.
</P> 
 
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT> 
<PRE>
 
ROBERT C. BAKER, ESQ., BAR ID #49255 
MELISSA S. BLUESTEIN, ESQ., BAR ID #130055 
PHILLIP A. BAKER, ESQ., BAR ID #169571 
