<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE> 
</HEAD> 
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" 
BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG 
SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV 
Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A> 
<P>

Defense lawyers accuses the plaintiffs of "playing to the media" in the discovery phase of 
the case. In this Aug. 26, 1996, pretrial motion, they say plaintiffs' lawyers deliberately 
asked potential witnesses for personal opinions on whether O.J. Simpson is guilty of 
murdering his former wife and Ronald Goldman in an effort to manufacture soundbites in 
the media and infect the jury pool. The defense says such opinions are irrelevant and 
should be excluded from the trial. 
</P> 

<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT> 
<PRE>
 
ROBERT C. BAKER, ESQ., BAR ID #49255 
MELISSA S. BLUESTEIN, ESQ., BAR ID #130055 
